                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d166">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710 Consultation 3/49b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-15T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 15, 1941—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1381. From the Under Secretary. Please tell Aranha that I have informed the
                    Chilean Ambassador here of our strong opinion that the consultative meeting
                    should be held in Rio, as was agreed in Habana in July 1940. The Ambassador, who
                    will transmit this view <pb facs="0139" n="129" xml:id="pg_129"/> to Santiago,
                    has expressed the belief that his Government will now desist from any efforts to
                    change the location of the meeting. [Welles.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
